  "text": "Can our existing knowledge be applied to understanding BEF relationships in a management context? Research on the interplay between food-web structure and ecosystem function can provide managers with a powerful tool to understand, predict, and manage ecosystems experiencing multiple competing demands and environmental perturbations. In some cases a food-web approach has already been effectively applied: for instance in marine fisheries management [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] and in studies of functional consequences of anthropogenic impacts on stream and river ecosystems [CITATION_3] (Box 2).",
